906a3c6d316a"],

Cell["\<\
This will be an important result when discussing properties of ideal gases \
obtained by considering particle motion, also known as the kinetic theory of \
gases.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921330884291374*^9, 
  3.9213309340882273`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"86b2dc1b-8e3e-42ad-933c-\
aa323b560c48"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Kinetic Theory of Gases", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9214207183165145`*^9, 
  3.9214207214495916`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"aef9d04c-f98a-4991-a54d-\
adeccf7a2e54"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Attributes of the Ideal Gas", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.92142221689861*^9, 
  3.9214222327380333`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fbe1f80d-a221-4230-bc0a-\
6ea60af12e6d"],

Cell["\<\
The kinetic theory of gases provides a simple analysis of an ideal gas that \
allows us to derive many of the fundamental properties relating to the motion \
of atoms or molecules. To begin, we will specify some of the attributes of an \
ideal gas.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9214222353064957`*^9, 
  3.9214223573411674`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ff1f8ede-1910-4bbe-989c-\
40939f67b209"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The gas is composed of point particles with equal mass ",
 StyleBox["m",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". The particles are considered to occupy no volume (which means the atomic \
or molecular volume is negligibly small in comparison to the unoccupied \
volume)."
}], "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921422394125749*^9, 
  3.921422477120496*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a76ce3d5-aac5-4af0-861e-\
8b22037f67c2"],

Cell["\<\
The gas particles do not experience any attractive or repulsive forces \
between one another.\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921422394125749*^9, 3.9214224480932074`*^9}, {
  3.9214224866093864`*^9, 
  3.921422566198086*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"afbb4ed3-f59d-448e-bec0-\
a0bb9aef3aa8"],

Cell["\<\
The motion of the particles is random and continuous (meaning no net motion \
of the gas particles).\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921422394125749*^9, 3.9214224480932074`*^9}, {
  3.9214224866093864`*^9, 
  3.9214226147903566`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a1452802-bf65-46dd-8236-\
4a09e51a1ac9"],

Cell["\<\
Collisions between gas particles or with container walls are elastic (no net \
loss of kinetic energy).\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921422394125749*^9, 3.9214224480932074`*^9}, {
  3.9214224866093864`*^9, 3.921422563896881*^9}, {3.921422621121272*^9, 
  3.9214226647980156`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1de25564-2c0c-4adf-8575-\
6480b86ae0b5"],

Cell["\<\
The motion of gas particles is isotropic, meaning (1) the probability of \
having a given velocity along each of the three Cartesian coordinates is \
independent of the other coordinates and (2) the distribution of particle \
velocities along a Cartesian coordinate is independent of direction.\
\>", "ItemNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921422394125749*^9, 3.9214224480932074`*^9}, {
  3.9214224866093864`*^9, 3.921422563896881*^9}, {3.921422621121272*^9, 
  3.9214228052146263`*^9}, {3.9214228926342845`*^9, 3.9214230217360773`*^9}, {
  3.921423055597267*^9, 
  3.921423056297391*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"963ee99a-1c8f-4157-9e58-\
30b914da1348"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Kinetic Theory and the Ideal Gas Law", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921488454744072*^9, 
  3.921488477501154*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"90015b14-1056-4f48-86ac-\
25050cd35685"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Consider an ideal gas confined to a box with ",
 StyleBox["x",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["y",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", and ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " dimensions given by ",
 StyleBox["j",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["k",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", and ",
 StyleBox["l",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". Let us examine the particles colliding with one of the walls of the box, \
taking one of the box walls in the ",
 StyleBox["zy",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "-plane as an example. The particles that collide with this wall will \
experience a change in their velocity in the ",
 StyleBox["x",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " direction, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[CapitalDelta]v", "x"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3b54cf9f-58e6-4214-aade-610369848e05"],
 ", of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"2", 
    SubscriptBox["v", "x"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "781a3e13-c3c0-4fcd-9821-e56c224f3047"],
 " (velocity is equal in magnitude but opposite in direction). The time \
between collisions of an individual particle with this wall will be ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"2", 
    RowBox[{"j", "/", 
     SubscriptBox["v", "x"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "44e80fa9-6982-4d23-848f-12299f6c44a0"],
 " (the time it takes the particle to traverse the entire ",
 StyleBox["x",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " dimension ",
 StyleBox["j",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and return to the wall)",
 ". We can write the rate of change of momentum, or force, experienced by \
these particles (and the wall) as "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9214887514551325`*^9, 3.921489015771431*^9}, {
  3.9214892005495462`*^9, 3.9214892074594755`*^9}, {3.921489238143817*^9, 
  3.9214894098367343`*^9}, {3.9214894490434*^9, 3.9214894670266247`*^9}, {
  3.92148960054091*^9, 
  3.9214896033910513`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c73894cd-eab8-4a35-ad0a-\
282be33f9acb"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["F",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], 
  StyleBox["=",
   FontSlant->"Plain"], 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox[
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox[
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["m",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[CapitalDelta]", 
       StyleBox["v",
        FontSlant->"Italic"]}]], 
     StyleBox["x",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
    StyleBox[
     RowBox[{"\[CapitalDelta]", 
      StyleBox["t",
       FontSlant->"Italic"]}]]], "=", 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["m",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      RowBox[{
       StyleBox["(",
        FontSlant->"Italic"], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["2",
         FontSlant->"Plain"], 
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["v",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], 
         StyleBox["x",
          FontSlant->"Italic"]]}], ")"}]}], 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"2", 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["j",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "/", 
        SubscriptBox[
         StyleBox["v",
          FontSlant->"Italic"], 
         StyleBox["x",
          FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}], ")"}]], "=", 
    FractionBox[
     SubsuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["mv",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["x",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
     StyleBox["j",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921489024557082*^9, 3.9214891005872407`*^9}, {
   3.921489134397932*^9, 3.921489136250597*^9}, 3.92148944128963*^9, {
   3.9214894730201235`*^9, 
   3.921489544380426*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f0c1609f-da44-44b1-858c-\
1509510f0bba"],

Cell["\<\
Note that this quantity is the force exerted by a single particle colliding \
with the wall. We can also write the pressure resulting from the collision of \
a particle with the wall as\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9214895729590683`*^9, 3.921489587993044*^9}, {
  3.9214896432070494`*^9, 
  3.921489660315482*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c4c6dfcc-58b6-4ac6-8ca0-\
c24f17b14bb0"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["P",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox[
    StyleBox["F",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["kl",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   StyleBox["=",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     SubsuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["mv",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["x",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
     StyleBox["jkl",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], "=", 
    FractionBox[
     SubsuperscriptBox[
      StyleBox["mv",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], 
      StyleBox["x",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
     StyleBox["V",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921489024557082*^9, 3.9214891005872407`*^9}, {
   3.921489134397932*^9, 3.921489136250597*^9}, 3.92148944128963*^9, {
   3.9214894730201235`*^9, 3.921489544380426*^9}, {3.921489670212925*^9, 
   3.9214897157230663`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8577b6d8-f32c-4941-8fb4-\
62887a4e977f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where ",
 StyleBox["V",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is the volume of the box. Now we must consider the sum over the ",
 StyleBox["N",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " particles in the box to obtain the total pressure,"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921489719314439*^9, 3.921489771955879*^9}, {
  3.921491551224578*^9, 
  3.921491557459714*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a95980ee-6aac-4a1a-a0b1-\
b17a1497017a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["P",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox[
    StyleBox["m",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["V",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{
    UnderoverscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["n",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", "1"}], "N"], 
    SubsuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["v",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["x",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921489024557082*^9, 3.9214891005872407`*^9}, {
   3.921489134397932*^9, 3.921489136250597*^9}, 3.92148944128963*^9, {
   3.9214894730201235`*^9, 3.921489544380426*^9}, {3.921489670212925*^9, 
   3.9214897157230663`*^9}, {3.921489792520482*^9, 3.921489803326991*^9}, {
   3.9214910505477448`*^9, 
   3.9214911046393394`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"33a87c4b-cf82-4256-8dfe-\
5fe9dc21f807"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If we now take the average value of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubsuperscriptBox[
   StyleBox["v",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["x",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.921489024557082*^9, 3.9214891005872407`*^9}, {
    3.921489134397932*^9, 3.921489136250597*^9}, 3.92148944128963*^9, {
    3.9214894730201235`*^9, 3.921489544380426*^9}, {3.921489670212925*^9, 
    3.9214897157230663`*^9}, {3.921489792520482*^9, 3.921489803326991*^9}, {
    3.9214910505477448`*^9, 3.9214911046393394`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "ffa1d6eb-6131-48b4-acda-4e87818284e1"],
 " as the sum over all values divided by the number of particles,  "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921491488232902*^9, 3.92149151115559*^9}, {
  3.9214915824970207`*^9, 
  3.9214915923087587`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"310234bd-1970-47b9-b594-\
b505129ec956"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["v",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], 
    StyleBox["x",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], "\[RightAngleBracket]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", 
    StyleBox["N",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{
    UnderoverscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["n",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", "1"}], "N"], 
    SubsuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["v",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["x",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921489024557082*^9, 3.9214891005872407`*^9}, {
   3.921489134397932*^9, 3.921489136250597*^9}, 3.92148944128963*^9, {
   3.9214894730201235`*^9, 3.921489544380426*^9}, {3.921489670212925*^9, 
   3.9214897157230663`*^9}, {3.921489792520482*^9, 3.921489803326991*^9}, {
   3.9214910505477448`*^9, 3.9214911046393394`*^9}, {3.921491518428946*^9, 
   3.9214915758951287`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"750ce911-6bb2-4a79-b0a3-\
a60d23f60315"],

Cell["we can rewrite our pressure expression as", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921491595171414*^9, 3.9214915998308144`*^9}, {
  3.921491634750886*^9, 
  3.921491636954965*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e77ebf66-c7ac-4df6-9200-\
fdc10e0e2c52"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  StyleBox["P",
   FontSlant->"Italic"], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{
     StyleBox["N",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], " ", 
     StyleBox["m",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]}], 
    StyleBox["V",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], 
    SubsuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["v",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["x",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], 
    "\[RightAngleBracket]"}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.921489024557082*^9, 3.9214891005872407`*^9}, {
   3.921489134397932*^9, 3.921489136250597*^9}, 3.92148944128963*^9, {
   3.9214894730201235`*^9, 3.921489544380426*^9}, {3.921489670212925*^9, 
   3.9214897157230663`*^9}, {3.921489792520482*^9, 3.921489803326991*^9}, {
   3.9214910505477448`*^9, 3.9214911046393394`*^9}, {3.9214916426400127`*^9, 
   3.92149164787847*^9}, {3.9214919106988215`*^9, 
   3.921491914791609*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c1ff7968-c680-4a17-9426-\
2bdf4564ad8e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Then, we can use the expression for",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["\[LeftAngleBracket]",
    FontSlant->"Plain"], 
   SuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["v",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "2"], "\[RightAngleBracket]"}]],
  InitializationCell->True,
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.9212505192469416`*^9, 3.921250534863843*^9}, {
