    3.9214245032022505`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "10503ca4-b6fb-45da-b532-b0f521ac259f"],
 ". It is important to note that all of these functions should be equal under \
our isotropic model. To find any one of these functions, we first take the \
partial derivative of equation (70) with respect to the velocity along the \
coordinate of interest. Using ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   SubscriptBox["v", "x"],
   FontSlant->"Italic"]],
  InitializationCell->True,
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.9212505192469416`*^9, 3.921250534863843*^9}, {
